body: Seems your installation of ffmpeg failed (this is a dependency of another package, so that shouldn't happen): `subprocess.CalledProcessError: Command 'ffprobe -i` -- if you search this error message in the github, you will find this. You can simply run `conda install -c conda-forge ffmpeg` in the environment.

Hi ecresp1el, 

I have faced the same issue and resolved it by removing the argument "save_frames = True" from the function deeplabcut.create_labeled_video. This argument must be having an issue with ffmpeg in the new DLC version (?)  

Here is my full story: 

Using the exact same setup as yours (Mac OS and installed DeepLabCut 2.1.9 via Anaconda env):

When I ran the function deeplabcut.create_labeled_video, I got the following error: 
> [Errno 2] No such file or directory: 'ffmpeg': 'ffmpeg'

Following the advice above, I ran **conda install -c conda-forge ffmpeg** while inside DeepLabCut env. 

This time, I got a new set of errors exactly as you mentioned in your last message. But removing the "save_frames = True" argument resolved it and I got the labeled video created.

The testscript passes on our systems, and here on our automated circle cli, so I don't think it's an issue with 2.1.9 @f-map (but if you want to roll back to 2.1.8.2, feel free to test it!). 

What would recommend for you both is to install from git, and be sure to run `./reinstll.sh` '(see here on how to be sure you are using the github latest code: https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut/wiki/How-to-use-the-latest-GitHub-code
